caller_intent: Jasmine wants to know the additional cost to add uninsured/underinsured motorist coverage (both bodily injury and property damage) to two vehicles on her policy.
resolution_steps: Jacy confirms Jasmine's identity and account details (name, address, policy information).
Jacy checks Jasmine's policy to verify existing coverage and vehicle details (Mazda 2006 and GMC 2025).
Jacy notes that the policy currently lacks the requested coverages and identifies a discrepancy in the document showing 'no cost' for some vehicles.
Jacy explains the need to consult National General (the carrier) for accurate pricing details.
Jacy offers to call Jasmine back with the information since the answer requires external verification.
knowledge_required: Understanding of insurance policy coverage details (uninsured/underinsured motorist)
Ability to interpret policy documents and carrier-specific pricing structures
Process for escalating to carrier representatives for precise cost information
summary: Jasmine inquired about the cost to add uninsured/underinsured motorist coverage to two vehicles on her policy. The agent verified her account, identified discrepancies in the policy document, and determined that a callback from the carrier was needed for accurate pricing. The agent offered to follow up with the information.
